🔷 What is HashSet?
HashSet is part of Java’s Collection Framework.
It implements the Set interface.
It stores unique elements only.
It is unordered (no indexing).
It is backed by a HashMap.
It allows null elements (only one).


✅ Key Features
| Feature                 | Description                               |
| ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| No Duplicates           | Stores only unique values                 |
| No Order Guaranteed     | Does not maintain insertion order         |
| Fast Performance        | Offers constant time for basic operations |
| Allows One `null` Value | Yes                                       |


✅ Commonly Used Methods
| Method               | Description                  |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `add(E e)`           | Adds an element              |
| `remove(Object o)`   | Removes the element          |
| `contains(Object o)` | Checks if the element exists |
| `isEmpty()`          | Checks if the set is empty   |
| `size()`             | Returns number of elements   |
| `clear()`            | Removes all elements         |
| `iterator()`         | Returns an iterator          |


🔸 Differences: HashSet vs TreeSet vs LinkedHashSet
| Feature       | `HashSet`        | `LinkedHashSet`           | `TreeSet`           |
| ------------- | ---------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------- |
| Order         | Unordered        | Maintains insertion order | Sorted (ascending)  |
| Performance   | Fastest          | Slightly slower           | Slower than HashSet |
| Null Elements | One null allowed | One null allowed          | No nulls allowed    |


✅ Summary
| Concept              | Details                                   |
| -------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Uniqueness           | Ensured using `hashCode()` and `equals()` |
| Duplicates allowed?  | ❌ No                                     |
| Order guaranteed?    | ❌ No                                     |
| Null values allowed? | ✅ Only one                               |
| Use when?            | Need fast lookup and uniqueness           |
